metadata.name: Stepping Stones #624
metadata.description:
"Stepping Stones" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Performance in Code: Deciphering Value in Generative Art, Art Basel Miami Beach, 2022

Stepping Stones explores the idea that the whole is greater than the sum of its parts. Simple patterns, shapes, textures, and colors are arranged in randomly selected ways. Overlaying shapes distort and blend, breaking these objects apart and causing complex forms to emerge. Combining these individual features together results in varying outcomes, from surprisingly simple to wildly chaotic.

---------------

Controls:
Press 1-6 to change the scale of the canvas (1 = default, 2500px x 2500px, 6 = 15,000px x 15,000px)
S (or double tap on mobile): Save output at current size
C: Toggle cutout shapes visibility
H: Toggle cutout outlines visibility
B: Iterate border sizes (none, default, 1.5x, 2x, 3x)
T: Toggle texture visibility
F: Toggle fullscreen
Add the url params x and y to set custom dimensions. For example, add &x=1500&y=500 for a 1500px x 500px image

---------------

Tyler Boswell (@teaboswell) 2022
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0, See bundle.js.LICENSE.txt for third party license information

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #700
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022

metadata.name: Udnē #492
metadata.description:
Udnē is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Performance in Code: Deciphering Value in Generative Art, Art Basel Miami Beach, 2022.

Udnē is a collection of asymmetric textural compositions. It's a search for creating harmonies and disharmonies by combining 3 colors with 3 unsynchronized mathematical equations. Udnē explores the beauty within triadic compositions while attempting to integrate two contrasting textures by forming instances of non-figurative scenes. The collection is a reflection of integrated and contrasting textures in micro and macro scale that we see in our everyday life environment.

You can press 's' in liveMode to save as 1000x1000px .png.

In liveMode, add '&density=7’ to the end of the URL to render at high resolution (7000x7000px). You can use 5, 7 or 10 for different resolutions. It will automatically download when the rendering is finished. 

Some compositions might take longer to render in low-performance computers. Please be patient and enjoy the process!

As a rare probability there is an intentionally kept glitch.

Made with p5js.
@distcollective, November 2022

metadata.name: Dapperu #706
metadata.description:
Go bold, Dapperu!

Dapperu is the first generative animated GIF avatar.

A single Dapperu has 13 traits that result in different colors, shapes and movements. Every Dapperu is unique and can be used as a GIF wherever you like.

You can right-click the image and save it as a GIF file.

You can also press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold outside the image] to save a ZIP file that contains the GIF and all individual frames as SVG images.

© 2022 Dapperu.

metadata.name: Modulation #6
metadata.description:
Isometric cityscapes, patterns and geometries generated by trigonometric functions and rendered as SVG.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 6000×7500.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=12000 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Hex-a-Sketch #1
metadata.description:
Truchet tiling with hexagons, drawn with three amounts of sketchiness in p5.js.  I had a lot of fun with this!  I love how it often looks like pastels, and sometimes like crayons.  Sometimes it reminds me of basket weaves or a quilt, or a warm sweater.  The super-sketchy can look chaotic, like it's trying to jump off the page, but if it weren't being made sketchy, then all the tiling would sync together in one form.  The foreground says, "look at me!" But then you notice the background with its nuance and depth.  It's like a dance between the two - the yin and the yang.  

I love sharing what I’ve learned about gen art and inspiring others on my YouTube channel, Steve’s Makerspace.

After clicking open:
press 2 - 5 to increase pixel density
press s to save a png

Resize goes back to pixel density 1.

metadata.name: Pixelnetika #29
metadata.description:
-------------------------------------------------

'drop it like it's raw'

-------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image - with finer details

right-click: save/copy image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine 
written in vanilla JavaScript
some more info in the source-code
The work will refresh and restart after some time
-------------------------------------------------

Pixelnetika - magnetic storms - Raw sketch 

-------------------------------------------------
Seen it in the past, whenever a group comes together.
Graffiti scene / Demo scene / Art scene etc. etc. 
New rules start popping up,
you should do this, you should do that..
Can't do this do this, you should not do that.
New rules, that can hinder you. 
If you start conforming/obeying the rules

Like seen people, making lovely works,
'but it should have more variations'
Adding all kinds of extras, 
that only made the work 
less powerful in the end

Or loosing themselves 
in the small details

Making 100 great and lovely sketches,
and finally releasing a work 
that totally did not work or sell at all.

Such a shame.


Well, it does not have enough variations

Variations: != 100 different extras?

For example, look at the Mark's Smoll-skulls or like Casey Reas works,
or like 100 warhol soup-cans, all just a littlebit different

I knew a classic composer, 
that really enjoyed creating works
when he was young.
Became a teacher,
conform within the institution
And lost all the joy he had for composing,
due to pressure and rules 'how things should be done'


Don't post too much

Some people like to work on 1 painting for years
trying to create their own Mona Lisa.

While Vincent van Gogh would paint lightning fast,
sometimes doing 1 painting a day


Break the rules
Make your own rules
set yourself free.
-------------------------------------------------

xxx Amsterdam chillout

For the love of Art, Polar bears, and throwing snowballs ^__^

August 12 2022

metadata.name: circle drops - 'the passenger' sketches #25
metadata.description:
-------------------------------------------------
The work will refresh and restart after some time

Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image - with finer details
: right-click: save/copy image
A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine 
written in vanilla JavaScript
some more info in the source-code
-------------------------------------------------

From a young age, 
I was exploring the fields around my parents house.

In the early spring. 
after the winter rains; 
and before the farmers would plant new crops.

Looking for fossils, 
old broken pottery with nice designs 
and stone artefacts.

One day I found a Neanderthal stone-axe, 
estimated like 70.000 years old,
wondered about the person that created it, 
how they lived and loved.

-------------------------------------------------

And I imagined like walking in a field or desert 
littered with sand and stones,
and having like an army of little robots 
slightly rearranging the area around me

-------------------------------------------------

For me Art 
is like a language

you can tell a story
create your own alphabet

Imagine, 

if aliens looked at your work,
or someone that lived 100.000 years ago

could it sparkle some magic
and feelings in their brain and soul?

would they like it? Need to understand it?

-------------------------------------------------

xxx amsterdam chillout

August 6, 2022
